  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Intervention to Support Orphaned Children after the 2014 Hostilities</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="3">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Orphans and guardians</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Provide 1,000 children orphaned by the summer 2014 hostilities with the following:

1) A monthly allowance for 12 months (NIS equivalent of $50 USD)

2) Clothing

3) Recreational activities

4) Monthly awareness sessions for orphan custodians on how to manage the physical and mental needs of children (96 monthly awareness sessions across all 5 Gaza governorates will be implemented.)

5) Vocational training support for 100 orphans over 16 years of age. This will include a 6 month course for men and women at the Gaza Technical and Vocational Training Centers in Gaza City an dKHan Younis. Course include hair dressing, child development, photography, electric or washing machine maintenance.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">To facilitate a decent standard of living for children orphaned by the summer 2014 hostilities</narrative>
  </description>
